cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a novel deep metric learning algorithm for cross-modal face recognition and object recognition databases. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also focuses on learning discriminative and generalizable models, which suggests that it could belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of neural networks, which could place it in cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with multimedia data, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia).
